data.enText: to get rid of sth that you no longer want or need

data.chText: 房间里到处是乱扔的报纸。
data.enText: The room was littered with discarded newspapers.

data.chText: 因天气炎热他脱掉了夹克。
data.enText: He had discarded his jacket because of the heat.

data.chText: 10% 的数据因不可靠而被废弃。
data.enText: 10% of the data was discarded as unreliable.

data.chText: 她现在可以打消晋升的念头了。
data.enText: She could now discard all thought of promotion.
to get rid of a card that you do not want

data.chText: 被抛弃的人（或物）；（尤指纸牌游戏中）垫出的牌
data.enText: a person or thing that is not wanted or thrown away, especially a card in a card game

simple_means.memory_skill: dis 去掉 + card 纸片 → 像扔〔废纸〕一样扔掉 → 抛弃

tr: getting rid something that is regarded as useless or undesirable
(cards) the act of throwing out a useless card or of failing to follow suit
anything that is cast aside or discarded

value.def: If you discard something, you get rid of it because you no longer want it or need it.

example.ex: Read the manufacturer's guidelines before discarding the box.
example.tran: 在丢掉盒子前先看一下制造商的使用说明。

partsOfSpeech.dec: carto〔= card〕纸片 + graph 写，画 + er 表人 → 绘制地图者
cart〔= card〕纸片 + on 表物 → 硬纸盒
cart 纸片 + oon 表物 → 纸片上的画 → 卡通画
chart 纸片 + er 表物 → 纸上的东西 → 契约
dis 去掉 + card 纸片 → 像扔〔废纸〕一样扔掉 → 抛弃
un 无 + chart 纸片 + ed 表形容词 → 纸〔地图〕上没有的 → 地图上未标明的
partsOfSpeech.d: 地图上未标明的；未知的
